goStruct.name: AnimeMetadataRequestedEvent
comments: AnimeMetadataRequestedEvent is triggered when anime metadata is requested and right before the metadata is processed.
This event is followed by [AnimeMetadataEvent] which is triggered when the metadata is available.
Prevent default to skip the default behavior and return the modified metadata.
If the modified metadata is nil, an error will be returned.

goStruct.name: AnimeMetadataEvent
comments: AnimeMetadataEvent is triggered when anime metadata is available and is about to be returned.
Anime metadata can be requested in many places, ranging from displaying the anime entry to starting a torrent stream.
This event is triggered after [AnimeMetadataRequestedEvent].
If the modified metadata is nil, an error will be returned.

goStruct.name: AnimeEpisodeMetadataRequestedEvent
comments: AnimeEpisodeMetadataRequestedEvent is triggered when anime episode metadata is requested.
Prevent default to skip the default behavior and return the overridden metadata.
This event is triggered before [AnimeEpisodeMetadataEvent].
If the modified episode metadata is nil, an empty EpisodeMetadata object will be returned.

goStruct.name: AnimeEpisodeMetadataEvent
comments: AnimeEpisodeMetadataEvent is triggered when anime episode metadata is available and is about to be returned.
In the current implementation, episode metadata is requested for display purposes. It is used to get a more complete metadata object since the original AnimeMetadata object is not complete.
This event is triggered after [AnimeEpisodeMetadataRequestedEvent].
If the modified episode metadata is nil, an empty EpisodeMetadata object will be returned.

goStruct.name: WatchHistoryItemRequestedEvent
comments: WatchHistoryItemRequestedEvent is triggered when a watch history item is requested.

Prevent default to skip getting the watch history item from the file cache, in this case the event should have a valid WatchHistoryItem object or set it to nil to indicate that the watch history item was not found.

goStruct.name: WatchHistoryItemUpdatedEvent
comments: WatchHistoryItemUpdatedEvent is triggered when a watch history item is updated.

goStruct.name: DebridAutoSelectTorrentsFetchedEvent
comments: DebridAutoSelectTorrentsFetchedEvent is triggered when the torrents are fetched for auto select.
The torrents are sorted by seeders from highest to lowest.
This event is triggered before the top 3 torrents are analyzed.

goStruct.name: DebridSkipStreamCheckEvent

fields.name: RetryDelay
comments: in seconds
DebridSkipStreamCheckEvent is triggered when the debrid client is about to skip the stream check.
Prevent default to enable the stream check.

goStruct.name: DebridSendStreamToMediaPlayerEvent
comments: DebridSendStreamToMediaPlayerEvent is triggered when the debrid client is about to send a stream to the media player.
Prevent default to skip the playback.

goStruct.name: DebridLocalDownloadRequestedEvent
comments: DebridLocalDownloadRequestedEvent is triggered when Seanime is about to download a debrid torrent locally.
Prevent default to skip the default download and override the download.

goStruct.name: DiscordPresenceAnimeActivityRequestedEvent
comments: DiscordPresenceAnimeActivityRequestedEvent is triggered when anime activity is requested, after the [animeActivity] is processed, and right before the activity is sent to queue.
There is no guarantee as to when or if the activity will be successfully sent to discord.
Note that this event is triggered every 6 seconds or so, avoid heavy processing or perform it only when the activity is changed.
Prevent default to stop the activity from being sent to discord.

goStruct.name: DiscordPresenceMangaActivityRequestedEvent
comments: DiscordPresenceMangaActivityRequestedEvent is triggered when manga activity is requested, after the [mangaActivity] is processed, and right before the activity is sent to queue.
There is no guarantee as to when or if the activity will be successfully sent to discord.
Note that this event is triggered every 6 seconds or so, avoid heavy processing or perform it only when the activity is changed.
Prevent default to stop the activity from being sent to discord.

goStruct.name: DiscordPresenceClientClosedEvent
comments: DiscordPresenceClientClosedEvent is triggered when the discord rpc client is closed.

goStruct.name: AnimeEntryRequestedEvent
comments: AnimeEntryRequestedEvent is triggered when an anime entry is requested.
Prevent default to skip the default behavior and return the modified entry.
This event is triggered before [AnimeEntryEvent].
If the modified entry is nil, an error will be returned.

goStruct.name: AnimeEntryEvent
comments: AnimeEntryEvent is triggered when the media entry is being returned.
This event is triggered after [AnimeEntryRequestedEvent].

goStruct.name: AnimeEntryFillerHydrationEvent
comments: AnimeEntryFillerHydrationEvent is triggered when the filler data is being added to the media entry.
This event is triggered after [AnimeEntryEvent].
Prevent default to skip the filler data.

goStruct.name: AnimeEntryLibraryDataRequestedEvent
comments: AnimeEntryLibraryDataRequestedEvent is triggered when the app requests the library data for a media entry.
This is triggered before [AnimeEntryLibraryDataEvent].

goStruct.name: AnimeEntryLibraryDataEvent
comments: AnimeEntryLibraryDataEvent is triggered when the library data is being added to the media entry.
This is triggered after [AnimeEntryLibraryDataRequestedEvent].

goStruct.name: AnimeEntryManualMatchBeforeSaveEvent
comments: AnimeEntryManualMatchBeforeSaveEvent is triggered when the user manually matches local files to a media entry.
Prevent default to skip saving the local files.

goStruct.name: MissingEpisodesRequestedEvent
comments: MissingEpisodesRequestedEvent is triggered when the user requests the missing episodes for the entire library.
Prevent default to skip the default process and return the modified missing episodes.

goStruct.name: MissingEpisodesEvent
comments: MissingEpisodesEvent is triggered when the missing episodes are being returned.

goStruct.name: AnimeLibraryCollectionRequestedEvent
comments: AnimeLibraryCollectionRequestedEvent is triggered when the user requests the library collection.
Prevent default to skip the default process and return the modified library collection.
If the modified library collection is nil, an error will be returned.

goStruct.name: AnimeLibraryCollectionEvent
comments: AnimeLibraryCollectionRequestedEvent is triggered when the user requests the library collection.

goStruct.name: AnimeLibraryStreamCollectionRequestedEvent
comments: AnimeLibraryStreamCollectionRequestedEvent is triggered when the user requests the library stream collection.
This is called when the user enables "Include in library" for either debrid/online/torrent streamings.

goStruct.name: AnimeLibraryStreamCollectionEvent
comments: AnimeLibraryStreamCollectionEvent is triggered when the library stream collection is being returned.

goStruct.name: AutoDownloaderRunStartedEvent
comments: AutoDownloaderRunStartedEvent is triggered when the autodownloader starts checking for new episodes.
Prevent default to abort the run.

goStruct.name: AutoDownloaderTorrentsFetchedEvent
comments: AutoDownloaderTorrentsFetchedEvent is triggered at the beginning of a run, when the autodownloader fetches torrents from the provider.

goStruct.name: AutoDownloaderMatchVerifiedEvent
comments: AutoDownloaderMatchVerifiedEvent is triggered when a torrent is verified to follow a rule.
Prevent default to abort the download if the match is found.

goStruct.name: AutoDownloaderSettingsUpdatedEvent
comments: AutoDownloaderSettingsUpdatedEvent is triggered when the autodownloader settings are updated

goStruct.name: AutoDownloaderBeforeDownloadTorrentEvent
comments: AutoDownloaderBeforeDownloadTorrentEvent is triggered when the autodownloader is about to download a torrent.
Prevent default to abort the download.

goStruct.name: AutoDownloaderAfterDownloadTorrentEvent
comments: AutoDownloaderAfterDownloadTorrentEvent is triggered when the autodownloader has downloaded a torrent.

goStruct.name: LocalFilePlaybackRequestedEvent
comments: LocalFilePlaybackRequestedEvent is triggered when a local file is requested to be played.
Prevent default to skip the default playback and override the playback.

goStruct.name: StreamPlaybackRequestedEvent
comments: StreamPlaybackRequestedEvent is triggered when a stream is requested to be played.
Prevent default to skip the default playback and override the playback.

goStruct.name: PlaybackBeforeTrackingEvent
comments: PlaybackBeforeTrackingEvent is triggered just before the playback tracking starts.
Prevent default to skip playback tracking.

goStruct.name: PlaybackLocalFileDetailsRequestedEvent
comments: PlaybackLocalFileDetailsRequestedEvent is triggered when the local files details for a specific path are requested.
This event is triggered right after the media player loads an episode.
The playback manager uses the local files details to track the progress, propose next episodes, etc.
In the current implementation, the details are fetched by selecting the local file from the database and making requests to retrieve the media and anime list entry.
Prevent default to skip the default fetching and override the details.

goStruct.name: PlaybackStreamDetailsRequestedEvent
comments: PlaybackStreamDetailsRequestedEvent is triggered when the stream details are requested.
Prevent default to skip the default fetching and override the details.
In the current implementation, the details are fetched by selecting the anime from the anime collection. If nothing is found, the stream is still tracked.

goStruct.name: ScanStartedEvent
comments: ScanStartedEvent is triggered when the scanning process begins.
Prevent default to skip the rest of the scanning process and return the local files.

goStruct.name: ScanFilePathsRetrievedEvent
comments: ScanFilePathsRetrievedEvent is triggered when the file paths to scan are retrieved.
The event includes file paths from all directories to scan.
The event includes file paths of local files that will be skipped.

goStruct.name: ScanLocalFilesParsedEvent
comments: ScanLocalFilesParsedEvent is triggered right after the file paths are parsed into local file objects.
The event does not include local files that are skipped.

goStruct.name: ScanCompletedEvent

fields.name: Duration
comments: in milliseconds
ScanCompletedEvent is triggered when the scanning process finishes.
The event includes all the local files (skipped and scanned) to be inserted as a new entry.
Right after this event, the local files will be inserted as a new entry.

goStruct.name: ScanMediaFetcherStartedEvent
comments: ScanMediaFetcherStartedEvent is triggered right before Seanime starts fetching media to be matched against the local files.

goStruct.name: ScanMediaFetcherCompletedEvent
comments: ScanMediaFetcherCompletedEvent is triggered when the media fetcher completes.
The event includes all the media fetched from AniList.
The event includes the media IDs that are not in the user's collection.

goStruct.name: ScanMatchingStartedEvent
comments: ScanMatchingStartedEvent is triggered when the matching process begins.
Prevent default to skip the default matching, in which case modified local files will be used.

goStruct.name: ScanLocalFileMatchedEvent
comments: ScanLocalFileMatchedEvent is triggered when a local file is matched with media and before the match is analyzed.
Prevent default to skip the default analysis and override the match.

goStruct.name: ScanMatchingCompletedEvent
comments: ScanMatchingCompletedEvent is triggered when the matching process completes.

goStruct.name: ScanHydrationStartedEvent
comments: ScanHydrationStartedEvent is triggered when the file hydration process begins.
Prevent default to skip the rest of the hydration process, in which case the event's local files will be used.

goStruct.name: ScanLocalFileHydrationStartedEvent
comments: ScanLocalFileHydrationStartedEvent is triggered when a local file's metadata is about to be hydrated.
Prevent default to skip the default hydration and override the hydration.

goStruct.name: ScanLocalFileHydratedEvent
comments: ScanLocalFileHydratedEvent is triggered when a local file's metadata is hydrated

goStruct.name: MangaEntryRequestedEvent
comments: MangaEntryRequestedEvent is triggered when a manga entry is requested.
Prevent default to skip the default behavior and return the modified entry.
If the modified entry is nil, an error will be returned.

goStruct.name: MangaEntryEvent
comments: MangaEntryEvent is triggered when the manga entry is being returned.

goStruct.name: MangaLibraryCollectionRequestedEvent
comments: MangaLibraryCollectionRequestedEvent is triggered when the manga library collection is being requested.

goStruct.name: MangaLibraryCollectionEvent
comments: MangaLibraryCollectionEvent is triggered when the manga library collection is being returned.

goStruct.name: MangaDownloadedChapterContainersRequestedEvent
comments: MangaDownloadedChapterContainersRequestedEvent is triggered when the manga downloaded chapter containers are being requested.
Prevent default to skip the default behavior and return the modified chapter containers.
If the modified chapter containers are nil, an error will be returned.

goStruct.name: MangaDownloadedChapterContainersEvent
comments: MangaDownloadedChapterContainersEvent is triggered when the manga downloaded chapter containers are being returned.

goStruct.name: MangaLatestChapterNumbersMapEvent
comments: MangaLatestChapterNumbersMapEvent is triggered when the manga latest chapter numbers map is being returned.

goStruct.name: MangaDownloadMapEvent
comments: MangaDownloadMapEvent is triggered when the manga download map has been updated.
This map is used to tell the client which chapters have been downloaded.

goStruct.name: MangaChapterContainerRequestedEvent
comments: MangaChapterContainerRequestedEvent is triggered when the manga chapter container is being requested.
This event happens before the chapter container is fetched from the cache or provider.
Prevent default to skip the default behavior and return the modified chapter container.
If the modified chapter container is nil, an error will be returned.

goStruct.name: MangaChapterContainerEvent
comments: MangaChapterContainerEvent is triggered when the manga chapter container is being returned.
This event happens after the chapter container is fetched from the cache or provider.

goStruct.name: MediaPlayerLocalFileTrackingRequestedEvent
comments: MediaPlayerLocalFileTrackingRequestedEvent is triggered when the playback manager wants to track the progress of a local file.
Prevent default to stop tracking.

goStruct.name: MediaPlayerStreamTrackingRequestedEvent
comments: MediaPlayerStreamTrackingRequestedEvent is triggered when the playback manager wants to track the progress of a stream.
Prevent default to stop tracking.

goStruct.name: PreUpdateEntryEvent
comments: PreUpdateEntryEvent is triggered when an entry is about to be updated.
Prevent default to skip the default update and override the update.

goStruct.name: PreUpdateEntryProgressEvent
comments: PreUpdateEntryProgressEvent is triggered when an entry's progress is about to be updated.
Prevent default to skip the default update and override the update.

goStruct.name: PreUpdateEntryRepeatEvent
comments: PreUpdateEntryRepeatEvent is triggered when an entry's repeat is about to be updated.
Prevent default to skip the default update and override the update.

goStruct.name: TorrentStreamAutoSelectTorrentsFetchedEvent
comments: TorrentStreamAutoSelectTorrentsFetchedEvent is triggered when the torrents are fetched for auto select.
The torrents are sorted by seeders from highest to lowest.
This event is triggered before the top 3 torrents are analyzed.

goStruct.name: TorrentStreamSendStreamToMediaPlayerEvent
comments: TorrentStreamSendStreamToMediaPlayerEvent is triggered when the torrent stream is about to send a stream to the media player.
Prevent default to skip the default playback and override the playback.
